The paper deals with the construction of maximum distance separable (mds) codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of algebraic systems and schemes suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cryptography (cs.CR) and data structures (cs.DS). The application of these codes in communication systems and error correction suggests that the paper may also be relevant to signal processing (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
